  is the linear operator defined by:

  
    
      
        
          ∂
          
            k
          
        
        (
        σ
        )
        =
        
          ∑
          
            i
            =
            0
          
          
            k
          
        
        (
        −
        1
        
          )
          
            i
          
        
        (
        
          v
          
            0
          
        
        ,
        …
        ,
        
          
            
              
                v
                
                  i
                
              
              ^
            
          
        
        ,
        …
        ,
        
          v
          
            k
          
        
        )
        ,
      
    
    {\displaystyle \partial _{k}(\sigma )=\sum _{i=0}^{k}(-1)^{i}(v_{0},\dots ,{\widehat {v_{i}}},\dots ,v_{k}),}
  where the oriented simplex

  
    
      
        (
        
          v
          
            0
          
        
        ,
        …
        ,
        
          
            
              
                v
                
                  i
                
              
              ^
            
          
        
        ,
        …
        ,
        
          v
          
